    "question": "An indifference curve through bundle $(4, 6)$ has $MRS = 2$. If the consumer gives up 1 unit of $y$, they need approximately **2 more units of $x$** to stay indifferent. **Drag the new bundle marker** to approximately $(6, 5)$.",
