    "explanation": "With $MRS = 2$: one unit of $x$ is worth 2 units of $y$ to this consumer. Losing 1 unit of $y$ requires gaining $1/2$ unit of $x$, moving to approximately $(4.5, 5)$. The MRS is the exchange rate along the indifference curve."
